Rating: 4
The first time I made this I followed the recipe almost to the letter. I can't help but to make small change; a splash of vanilla and sprinkle of this or that. The topping is what is important to my review. The first time I dropped the topping on by the spoonfuls. Perfect! It's fluffy and light. Today, I made it with granny smith apples and it turned out well. I wasn't afraid to serve it to my neighbors. Only, I got the idea that if I spread the topping over the baked apples it might trap some moisture in the dish because the apples were looking a little dry when I pulled them out. It did trap the moisture and it melded it together. It wasn't unpleasant but next time I'm dropping the spoonfuls over the pan so it marks off the servings. That way, it's like getting your own little crunchy cookie top on the fruit. This is a good recipe for someone who isnt a talented baker. Its super easy and recommended for someone who needs a dessert but doesnt really bake. For people like me, who love to bake, it likes to be played with. Enjoy your ovens

