Took suggestions from others. Used cinnamon, used buttermilk instead of hot water. (Powdered buttermilk is a great staple to keep.) Make sure to add some salt to peaches; anything this sweet needs a little salt. Also added 2 tbl. wheat germ to topping to give more depth. Had "vision problem" with hot water, couldn't see using it in pastry. Cold buttermilk much better. Also, this recipe cries out for using a food processor for topping.

