Very good dessert. I made some more modifications that worked VERY well. First, I sprinkled some cinnamon on top of the peaches before baking, and that added some good flavor to the dessert. For the biscuit topping, I added 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, and 1 teaspoon lemon peel. I agree with the previous reviewer who said that more topping should be made, especially if you're using a large dish where your peaches are more spread out. I also agree that the peach wedges should not be too thin. Some of my pieces just got too mushy. Finally, it's a good idea to find peaches that are not yet too soft. I'd say medium-ripe would be the most appropriate "degree." Top with vanilla ice-cream and you're good to go.

