This rates better than 3 forks, but isn't perfect, so I can't give it 4 forks. I made this recipe 3 times in a span of 7 days! I love the biscuit-y topping (used the water from blanching the peaches for extra flavor; sprinkled toasted sliced almonds and cinnamon sugar on top). I also added cloves and ginger powder (grated fresh ginger might be better) to the peach mixture. I'll keep playing around with the spices in the peaches. So far, it's my favorite cobbler recipe. Note to those who can't get fresh peaches: use frozen--tastes so much better than canned in a cobbler.

