This is a fantastic baseline recipe for cobbler. I made the following modifications: used brown sugar rather than white; added 1/2 t. cinnamon and 1/4 t. cardamom; increased cornstarch to 1T. (I prefer a slighter tighter consistency) and baked the whole thing in a (buttered) 8" cast iron skillet. (Also, I peeled the peaches.) My guests raved and my husband proclaimed it the best cobbler ever! This is definately going to become a standard in our house.

